    "README.md",
    "21296b0b4a8490b3901d769225efbdb3f3a2c4b4d13d0b5b15c8e61a30d6f0f4",
    nu-agent,
    [
      "Enrichment Contract"
    ],
    "``nu-agent``
 is designed to enrich one record at a time.
Input: one structured record plus a target schema and prompt
Output: one validated JSON result on stdout
Errors: diagnostics on stderr and non-zero exit code
Batch iteration, retries across a dataset, and persistence live in a separate batch tool
``enrich``
 is the stable single-item entrypoint
Recommended caller pattern:
```nu
let result = (try {
  ./nu-agent --task \"annotate workout\" --record '{\"exercise\":\"squat\"}' --schema '{\"allowed\":[\"exercise\"],\"required\":[\"exercise\"],\"non_null\":[\"exercise\"]}' --validate-only
} catch { |err|
  error make { msg: ($err.msg? | default \"nu-agent enrichment failed\") }
})

```
For now, keep stderr free-form and let Nushell 
``try/catch``
 handle failures. Do not depend on parsing stderr as JSON.
",
    {
      commands: [

      ],
      tags: [
        high_priority
      ],
      idiom_weight: 1
    },
    "Title: nu-agent
Path: Enrichment Contract
Content:
``nu-agent``
 is designed to enrich one record at a time.
Input: one structured record plus a target schema and prompt
Output: one validated JSON result on stdout
Errors: diagnostics on stderr and non-zero exit code
Batch iteration, retries across a dataset, and persistence live in a separate batch tool
``enrich``
 is the stable single-item entrypoint
Recommended caller pattern:
```nu
let result = (try {
  ./nu-agent --task \"annotate workout\" --record '{\"exercise\":\"squat\"}' --schema '{\"allowed\":[\"exercise\"],\"required\":[\"exercise\"],\"non_null\":[\"exercise\"]}' --validate-only
} catch { |err|
  error make { msg: ($err.msg? | default \"nu-agent enrichment failed\") }
})

```
For now, keep stderr free-form and let Nushell 
``try/catch``
 handle failures. Do not depend on parsing stderr as JSON.
"
