This runs the shredder, normalises chunk/command data, emits embedding inputs,

and (when 
``embed_runner``
 is available) writes deterministic embeddings into

``--out-dir/embeddings/``
.
Querying the artefacts
```nu
use ./tools.nu *

resolve-command-doc --name \"open\"

search-nu-concepts --query \"pipeline\" --limit 3

```
You can also run 
``target/debug/nu-search``
 directly against the generated

embeddings for quick similarity checks.
