    ],
    "The book is split into chapters which are further broken down into sections.

You can click on the chapter headers to get more information about it.
[link: installation.md] Installation
, of course, helps you get Nushell onto your system.
[link: getting_started.md] Getting Started
 shows you the ropes. It also explains some of the design principles where Nushell differs from typical shells, such as Bash.
[link: nu_fundamentals.md] Nu Fundamentals
 explains basic concepts of the Nushell language.
[link: programming_in_nu.md] Programming in Nu
 dives more deeply into the language features and shows several ways how to organize and structure your code.
[link: nu_as_a_shell.md] Nu as a Shell
 focuses on the shell features, most notably the configuration and environment.
[link: coming_to_nu.md] Coming to Nu
 is intended to give a quick start for users coming from other shells or languages.
[link: design_notes.md] Design Notes
 has in-depth explanation of some of the Nushell's design choices.
[link: advanced.md] (Not So) Advanced
 includes some more advanced topics (they are not 
so
 advanced, make sure to check them out, too!).
